ABOUT
======
This module will strip control codes (bold/underline/reverse) if
chanmode +S is set, and will block such messages if the chan is +c.
 
REQUIRES
=========
This module works on UnrealIRCd 3.2 and UnrealIRCd 4.

INSTALL
========
Just run: ./build

CONFIG
=======
All you need to do is add the loadmodule line to your unrealircd.conf:

For UnrealIRCd 3.2.x:
loadmodule "src/modules/nocodes.so";

For UnrealIRCd 4:
loadmodule "third/nocodes";
